**Findings**

1. The new claim that composition children should not be venue-adapter eligible breaks the motivating use case. In the current pipeline, downstream/upstream BFS only builds token-token structure; lending-market `PLEDGE`/`LEND` edges come from venue adapters, and those adapters are explicitly filtered to `upstream_ids` only. If xUSD-like composition descendants are excluded from any adapter eligibility set, the graph still will not gain the Morpho/Aave/Euler collateral edges needed for cycle detection. The proposed fallback, “BFS re-entry should discover this via Enso,” is not true in this codebase. See [context-snapshot.md#L523](/Users/v/Code_2026/heated-debate/debates/vault-composition-adapter-review/context-snapshot.md#L523), [context-snapshot.md#L605](/Users/v/Code_2026/heated-debate/debates/vault-composition-adapter-review/context-snapshot.md#L605), and [neigh_adapter_morpho.py](/Users/v/Code_2026/heated-debate/neigh/neigh_adapter_morpho.py).

2. “Best-confidence path” is still the wrong opacity model once weights exist. If 20% of exposure reaches a leaf through an on-chain path and 80% through a manual path, picking the strongest path per leaf misclassifies the full leaf as high-confidence. Opacity needs contribution-level accounting by path weight and proof class, not one winner per leaf. The current traversal already collapses alternative paths at the node level, so this is not a small scorer tweak. See [context-snapshot.md#L957](/Users/v/Code_2026/heated-debate/debates/vault-composition-adapter-review/context-snapshot.md#L957) and [context-snapshot.md#L1456](/Users/v/Code_2026/heated-debate/debates/vault-composition-adapter-review/context-snapshot.md#L1456).

3. `EdgeEvidence[]` solves provenance loss but not quantitative conflicts. One semantic edge can now carry multiple sources, but Round 3 never defines which weight is operative when evidence disagrees or is incomplete. “Append evidence, traverse one edge” is fine for topology, but weighted blast/opacity/exit still need a canonical allocation value or conservative merge rule. Without that, the risk engine has proof metadata but no usable numeric semantics. See [context-snapshot.md#L1215](/Users/v/Code_2026/heated-debate/debates/vault-composition-adapter-review/context-snapshot.md#L1215), [context-snapshot.md#L1242](/Users/v/Code_2026/heated-debate/debates/vault-composition-adapter-review/context-snapshot.md#L1242), and [context-snapshot.md#L1397](/Users/v/Code_2026/heated-debate/debates/vault-composition-adapter-review/context-snapshot.md#L1397).

4. Path-product weighting still lacks a mass-conservation policy. In a DAG with convergent descendants, naive weighted traversal can double count the same downstream exposure; in a cyclic manifest, it becomes undefined. Depth-relaxation fixes traversal order, not accounting correctness. The design needs an explicit rule for convergent paths and manifest cycles: reject them, condense SCCs, or define capped contribution semantics. See [context-snapshot.md#L1456](/Users/v/Code_2026/heated-debate/debates/vault-composition-adapter-review/context-snapshot.md#L1456).

**Open Questions**

- What is the intended adapter eligibility set for venue enrichment if `upstream_ids` stays root-centric? A separate `adapter_seed_ids` is plausible, but it needs a scope rule or the graph will sprawl.
- Are manifest weights meant to represent current portfolio allocation, redemption entitlement, or worst-case exposure bound? Blast radius, exit liquidity, and opacity do not use the same semantics.
- Are cyclic or recursively opaque manifests valid input? If yes, the accounting model needs SCC semantics. If no, validation should reject them up front.

Round 3 is stronger because it finally acknowledges weighted risk semantics and the traversal/path issue. The remaining gap is that it still treats provenance and weights as attachable metadata, when the hard part is defining how those values compose into one root-to-leaf exposure model.
